[{"location":"#QuantumChaos","page":"Home","title":"QuantumChaos","text":"(Image: Build Status)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Install","page":"Home","title":"Install","text":"julia>]\npkg> add QuantumChaos\n\nCheck the installed version:\n\n]st QuantumChaos\n\nStart using the package:\n\nusing QuantumChaos","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quickstart","page":"Home","title":"Quickstart","text":"As a quickstart example we can solve the rectangular billiard.\n\nWe start by using the package:\n\nusing QuantumChaos\n\nThen we define the geometry of the rectangular billiard B:\n\nB = RectBilliard(1.0,       # Lenght along x\n                sqrt(2),    # Lenght along y\n                100,        # Number of points along x\n                200)        # Number of points along y\n\nHaving defined the geometry we can build the Hamiltonian ham on B which corresponds to the laplacian operator:\n\nham = rect_laplacian(B)\n\nWe now want to compute the first k=20 eigenvalues E_num using ArnoldiMethod:\n\nk = 20\n\ndecomp, history = partialschur(ham, nev=k, tol=1e-6, which=:SR)  \nhistory\nE_num, Î¨_vecs = partialeigen(decomp)\n\nTo check that these are the right eigenvalues we can compare them to the analytical solutions E_ana using the built-in function analytical_energies:\n\nE_ana = analytical_energies(B, k)","category":"section"},{"location":"#More-in-depth-summary","page":"Home","title":"More in-depth summary","text":"With this package we can solve numerically two kind of billiards: the rectangular billiard and the Bunimovich stadium. The last one shows quantum chaos behavior.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Rectangular-billiard","page":"Home","title":"Rectangular billiard","text":"For the rectangular quantum billiard we want to find the eigenvalues and the eigenvectors: to do this we solve the Helmoltz equation over a rectangular grid using the Finite Difference Method (FDM).\n\nFor a more in depth discussion refer to this link.","category":"section"},{"location":"#To-do-list","page":"Home","title":"To-do list","text":"[x] Test eigenfunctions rect;\n[] Test eigenfunctions stadium;\n[] Divide plot functions;\n[] Symmetry sectors for stadium;","category":"section"}]
